#mothersday

We often get asked what our Upcycled Sunflower Protein is. This video will give you the gist, but more importantly, let's dig into the why.

In the US, food waste is estimated at between 30-40% of the food supply (😱). And while waste happens along any stage of the supply chain, we are partnering with local farmers and suppliers to identify inefficiencies from the ground up. This is how we unearthed the power of Upcycled Sunflower Protein.

When you consider all the water, energy and resources it takes to grow food, it will always make the most economic and environmental sense to find innovative ways to use the whole seed vs growing new. For us, upcycled sunflower seeds are just the start. There's a big food industry out there with a lot of waste and we're ready to roll up our sleeves 💪

#upcycle #upcycling #regenerative #bthechange #sustainableagriculture #regenerativeagriculture

latestIgtvVideos.title: Earth Day Check-In with our Local Farmers 🌾
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
For farmers, there's no such thing as Earth Day. When your livelihood is the soil itself, Earth Day is a 365 day, year after year, generation after generation effort. So today, we turn it over to a few of our local farmers so they can explain why soil health is everything (for them and for you!) and what we, as consumers, can do to to help support soil health. 

Thank you to @aframefarm + @askegaardorganicfarm + @grasswayfarmiowa for graciously sharing your knowledge during the busiest time of year.

Today through Sunday, we're celebrating family farmer's ongoing commitment to care for our earth with 20% off site wide on sevensundays.com! Use code THANKSFARMERS at checkout.

latestIgtvVideos.title: An Up-Close Look at Soil Health with A-Frame Farms
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
"I've been farming this farm for four years, and there wasn't a worm when we started. To be honest, it was like concrete. Look at the tilth of this soil right now. It blows my mind to think that I can dig down into this ground because I know what it was like when we started." -@aframefarm⁠
⁠
We get it... "soil health" is not a sexy or flashy or trendy topic, but today is #WorldSoilDay and it's more important than ever to shed some light on damaged dirt.⁠
⁠
We love this video from Luke Peterson of @aframefarm digging through the soil in his first ever field of buckwheat that he planted for us this year. You can see and feel his child-like wonder and passion witnessing first hand how his soil has gone from virtually concrete to the lush, moist, rich, worm-filled soil he runs his fingers through in just four years. The soil is alive again. It is healthy. It holds nutrients. It is regenerative. It is part of the solution.⁠
⁠
2020 gave us crisis after crisis. It can feel overwhelming as an individual or a business to know how and where to help. But if there's one thing we've learned from our farmers, it's that diverse crops create living soil, and living soil is the basis for the healthy and sustainable food system we so desperately need more of.⁠
⁠
This living soil depends on a farmer who operates a regenerative, diverse cropping system with carefully managed livestock grazing. The farmer depends on a market and fair pricing that supports these diverse crops, which is where Seven Sundays and other food companies can play a role. And Seven Sundays depends on buyers and consumers who care (like all of you who have read this far) where we source our ingredients and who are willing to vote with their dollars on small ethically-run businesses.⁠
⁠
As our world becomes more digitally connected, we find ourselves more disconnected to the very earth and land that feeds us. Let's get our hands dirty together and fight for the health of our soils. Our future depends on it.⁠
⁠
#worldsoilday #4soil #SoilBiodiversity #FutureofFood ⁠
⁠

latestPosts.caption:
Super Fruity Cereal Bars 🍓🍒

Look at all those gorgeous colors! 🌈 This super simple recipe from our pal @feastingonfruit is giving us all the vibrant vibes. Every hue comes straight from real fruit (like tart cherries, strawberries, and beets). Turns out the best rainbow comes from the garden, not a chemistry set! #keepitreal

INGREDIENTS 🥣
6 c. Super Fruity Oat Protein Cereal
¾ c. coconut or cashew butter
½ c. honey
1 tsp. vanilla extract
½ c. dairy-free white chocolate chips

DIRECTIONS 🧑‍🍳
1. Pour the cereal into a large mixing bowl.
2. In a separate bowl, combine the nut butter and sweetener. Microwave 30 seconds to melt. Add the vanilla, and whisk until smooth.
3. Pour over top of the cereal, and mix to evenly coat. Press very firmly into an 8x8” square pan lined with parchment paper. Chill overnight.
4. Remove from the pan, and slice into squares.
5. Dip the bottoms in melted white chocolate. Place on a pan lined with wax paper, and place back in the fridge until the chocolate is set.
6. Enjoy! Store in an airtight container in the fridge for up to 2 weeks.
